                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d670">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1731/168: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-02T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 2, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Your 46, February 29, 11 a.m.</p>
                <p>Point 7. In view of your assurances that we would not be waiving any rights by
                    agreeing to giving Nicaragua in memorandum form the first two sentences quoted
                    under this point in the Department’s telegram No. 14 of February 22, 8 p.m., you
                    are authorized to agree to do so. The Department still regards this as an
                    undesirable procedure, however, and wishes you not to use this authority except
                    as a last resort.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
